description.narrative:
The overall objective of the project is to contribute to the improvement of the quality of Congolese democracy by conducting rigorous research into political parties and civil society organizations, creating mechanisms to strengthen state accountability, and stimulating debates on better governance.
Specifically, this project aims to:
Conduct in-depth comparative studies on the formal and informal accountability mechanisms which already exist within the main political parties and civil society organizations in the DRC in order to understand existing patterns of accountability;
Carry out regular polling across the Congo in order to gain a better understanding of the priorities of the broader public, and to inform politicians of their popularity;
Monitor the activities of elected members of parliament and the government in key areas (justice, security, and anti-corruption reforms) through a website and infographics disseminated on social media;
Stimulate and engage in a public debate around accountability in the Congo, drawing on our research and leading up to 2023 elections, by setting up a CRG office in Kinshasa, broadcasting a podcast on local radio stations, and holding a series of public debates across the country.
